field.name: Epoch
field.description: Ephemeris Time of the start of the accumulation for this measurement.

field.name: UTC
field.description: The time of the start of the measurement in as a UTC time string (CCYY-DOYTHH:MM:SS.hhh)

field.name: DDOY
field.description: The decimal day of year of the time at MidET

field.name: ET
field.description: The ephemeris time at the start of the spin group.

field.name: MidET
field.description: The ephemeris time at the centered at the mid-point of the spin group.

field.name: StopET
field.description: The ephemeris time at the end of the spin group.

field.name: Duration
field.description: Duration of the spin group.

field.name: OrbitNumber
field.description: Orbit Number at the time of the measurement.

field.name: Spin
field.description: The spin number as identified by the spacecraft at the beginning of the measurement(cyclical value)

field.name: FEDU
field.description: Directional Differential protons Flux one record per spin binned by pitch angle in 17 bins (9.99999999000001 degrees with 15 degree outer bins): Counts/(MeV-cm^2-s-sr)

field.name: FEDU_Weight
field.description: Weighting factors used to calculate spin integration of differential flux indicating the number of observations made for each energy channel/bin combination per spin

field.name: FEDU_PerpPressure
field.description: Calculated protons perpendicular partial pressure for energies: 20Kev-940KeV. Does not include noisy energy channels.

field.name: FEDU_ParaPressure
field.description: Calculated protons parallel partial pressure for energies: 20Kev-940KeV. Does not include noisy energy channels.

field.name: FEDU_Density
field.description: The Number Density (#/cm^3) calculated by integrating the distribution function over energy (20Kev-940KeV) and pitch angle for the species. Does not include noisy energy channels.

field.name: FEDU_IntegralFlux
field.description: Pitch Angle Integrated and Energy Integrated total intensity of particles per second observed during the spin for energies: 20Kev-940KeV. Does not include noisy energy channels.

field.name: FEDU_OmniFlux
field.description: Omni Directional Total Flux per spin for energies: 20Kev-940KeV (Counts/(MeV-s-cm^2))

field.name: FEDU_MinimFlux
field.description: Observed minimum intensity in the spin for each energy channel measured (20Kev-940KeV): Counts/(MeV-cm^2-s)

field.name: FEDU_MaximFlux
field.description: Observed maximum intensity in the spin for each energy channel measured (20Kev-940KeV): Counts/(MeV-cm^2-s)

field.name: FEDU_Error
field.description: The Poisson statistical counting percentage error of the measurement for each energy channel and bin calculated as 1/sqrt(Counts)*100.

field.name: FEDU_Energy
field.description: Midpoint energy of each measurement channel in MeV. A value of -1 indicates that an energy definition for this channel is not applicable

field.name: FEDU_EnergyRange
field.description: Minimum and Maximum energy in MeV of the measurement channel. A value of -1 indicates that either an energy definition for this channel is not applicable or that the upper end of the channel is undefined - i.e. the channel becomes integral.

field.name: FEDU_Quality
field.description: Quality flag for the measurement for each pitch angle bin/timestep. see PREBM standards for definition

field.name: Position
field.description: The position of the SC at MidET in the GEO Reference Frame.

field.name: Position_SM
field.description: Position of the spacecraft at MidET in the SM (Solar Magnetospheric) reference frame using the definition SPICE kernels available at production. The position varies with time and contains the position for the X, Y, and Z axis of the SC in Earth Radii.

field.name: Position_GSM
field.description: The position of the SC at MidET in the GSM Reference Frame.

field.name: Position_Quality
field.description: The position quality flag, 0=good, 1=bad.

field.name: L
field.description: Dipole L value at MidET calculated using the SM Reference Frame and taken from the definitive SPICE SPK kernels that are available at the time.

field.name: MLT
field.description: The Magnetic Local Time of S/C at MidET in Centerted Dipole Coordinates derived from ECT MagEphem data.

field.name: L_Eq
field.description: The McElqain L value at MidET calculated at the Equator (derived from ECT MagEphem data) using the OP77Q field model.

field.name: L_Star
field.description: The Roeder's L* value at MidET (derived from ECT MagEphem data) for the average pitch angle using the OP77Q field model.

field.name: I
field.description: The Integral invariant at MidET for the average pitch angle derived from ECT MagEphem data using the OP77Q field model.

field.name: PA_Midpoint
field.description: Center-point pitch angle in Degrees.

field.name: PA_Range
field.description: Pitch Angle Range as minimum value and maximum value for each PA bin.
